OL,5, Advertising breaks on UK television    
OL,6, channels could get longer and more     
OL,7, frequent as part of a review of        
OL,8, broadcasting rules by regulator Ofcom. 
OL,10,FThe frequency and length of advertising
OL,11,Fwill be reassessed in light of evolving
OL,12,Fviewing habits and the rise of         
OL,13,Fstreaming services, Ofcom said.        
OL,15,FThe regulator pledged to "listen to    
OL,16,Fdifferent views and examine what TV    
OL,17,Fviewers say" before any changes.       
OL,19,FIt previously said the frequency of ads
OL,20,Fcould be seen as disruptive to viewing.
